-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Dec 03, 2014 10:30AM EST
-- None



Dec 3 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1530 GMT on Wednesday:

** EU antitrust regulators are likely to expand their scrutiny of French telecoms provider Orange's <ORAN.PA> 3.4-billion-euro ($4.2 billion) bid for Jazztel <JAZ.MC> after the companies failed to allay their concerns, two sources familiar with the matter said on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0TN346]  ** Barrick Gold Corp <ABX.TO> said on Wednesday it had formed a joint venture with Saudi Arabian Mining Co <1211.SE> to run the Jabal Sayid copper asset in the kingdom, which will jump-start output at the long-delayed mine. [ID:nL2N0TN0S0]  ** Advent International and its partner, the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, are still keen on buying nationalized lender Hypo Alpe Adria's Balkan network and will meet Austrian Finance Minister Hans Joerg Schelling soon on this, the minister said on Wednesday. [ID:nV9N0P500R]  ** Chesnara Plc <CSN.L> said it would buy Netherlands-based Waard Group for 67.8 million euros ($83.9 million), the first acquisition by the insurance-focused takeover specialist in more than a year.[ID:nL3N0TN2H3]  ** Johnson & Johnson <JNJ.N>, the U.S.-based healthcare company, has hired Goldman Sachs <GS.N> to explore a sale of its artificial sweetener brand Splenda, sources familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL6N0TN37J]  ** Indonesia expects to sign agreements with China's CNOOC Ltd <0883.HK>, Saudi Aramco and two other oil companies next week covering direct oil sales and refinery investments in Southeast Asia's largest economy, a senior Pertamina official said. [ID:nL3N0TN2WC]  ** German property lender Aareal <ARLG.DE> is seeing its chances of buying peer Westimmo [WDLGW.UL] rise after other bidders have lost interest, said several sources familiar with the transaction. [ID:nL6N0TN32I]  ** TPG is exiting its whole investment in car dealership China Grand Automotive Services through a sale to Haitong International Securities Group Ltd <0665.HK> and a third party investor, according to regulatory filings and sources close to the transaction. [ID:nL6N0TI37D]  ** Nordic telecom operators Telenor <TEL.OL> and TeliaSonera <TLSN.ST> will merge their Danish operations to cut costs and improve profitability in a market where both face tough competition and weak economic growth. [ID:nL6N0TN0MY]  ** Turkey's state-run lender Halkbank said late on Tuesday that its offer to buy a 76.76 percent stake in Serbian lender Cacanska Banka had failed. [ID:nL6N0TN0RS]